record_data.record_plain_text: PPL ENERGYPLUS, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FOR THE SALE, ASSIGNMENT, OR TRANSFER OF TRANSMISSION RIGHTS ON NON-JURISDICTIONAL TRANSMITTING UTILITY SYSTEMS General Purpose: The purpose of this rate schedule is to provide for the sale, assignment, or transfer of transmission rights by PPL EnergyPlus, LLC ("PPL EnergyPlus") on non-jurisdictional transmitting utility systems as to which the transmission provider does not play the intermediary role in secondary market transmission transactions as contemplated by the reforms that the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("Commission") adopted in Order No. 890. Duration: This rate schedule shall continue in effect until terminated or changed and such termination or change becomes effective in accordance with any applicable regulatory requirements. Services To Be Rendered: PPL EnergyPlus may sell, assign, or transfer to a purchaser, pursuant to an agreement negotiated between PPL EnergyPlus and purchaser, all or a portion of PPL EnergyPlus' rights to the use of the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility system that PPL EnergyPlus has reserved for its own use under a service agreement with the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility or under a service agreement it has acquired from another customer. The purchaser must be an eligible customer pursuant to the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility's open access transmission tariff or other tariffs pursuant to which the transmission rights to be transferred to the purchaser were originally obtained from the transmission provider. Sale of Transmission Rights: PPL EnergyPlus may sell transmission rights that PPL EnergyPlus has reserved for its own use from the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility. PPL EnergyPlus may sell, assign, or transfer such transmission rights at the price provided below. Terms and Conditions: Except for price, the terms and conditions pursuant to which PPL EnergyPlus will sell, assign, or transfer transmission rights on the non-jurisdictional transmitting utility system to a purchaser shall be the terms and conditions governing the original grant of such transmission rights by the transmission provider. Compensation: PPL EnergyPlus shall sell, assign, or transfer any transmission rights pursuant to this rate schedule at a price mutually agreed to between PPL EnergyPlus and purchaser, provided, however, that it shall not make sales at prices higher than those permitted by the Bonneville Power Administration ("BPA") open access transmission tariff unless and until the Commission may indicate that the resale price restriction in BPA's open access transmission tariff is appropriate. Modifications: PPL EnergyPlus unilaterally may apply to the Commission or other regulatory agency having jurisdiction for a modification of this rate schedule pursuant to section 205 of the Federal Power Act and the regulations promulgated thereunder. Electric Quarterly Reports: In its Electric Quarterly Reports, pursuant to Commission guidance, PPL EnergyPlus will provide to the Commission data concerning transmission capacity sales, assignments, or transfers by PPL EnergyPlus on any non-jurisdictional transmitting utility systems to the extent such transactions are entered into pursuant to this rate schedule.
